19/05/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The UN envoy tasked with the Greece-Macedonia name dispute, US Ambassador Matthew Nimitz, was expected to hold talks in Skopje Thursday (19 May).
Nimitz said the purpose of his visit was to "exchange opinions with the authorities and to see if any progress could be achieved".
The diplomat will meet with Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski, Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski and Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva.
In other news, Macedonia's Parliament on Wednesday unanimously endorsed the government's initiative for changes in the Macedonian Constitution related to the country's bid to move closer to EU membership.
The legislature decided that the cabinet should elaborate and present draft amendments on the main law within 60 days.
According to Justice Minister Meri Mladenovska-Gjorgjievska, the adjustments will be aimed at restructuring the judiciary, in line with EU standards.
(Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax - 19/05/05;
A1 TV, Telma TV - 18/05/05)
